
HOW TO COMPILE SPECFEM2D

(requires gfortran, MPI)


1. Download SPECFEM2D source code:

>> git clone https://github.com/SPECFEM/specfem2D.git
>> cd specfem2D


2. To make sure our results can be exactly reproduced, we specify a particular
version of the code using its Git hash. To obtain this specific version:

>> git reset --hard ccc2b928


3. Compile SPECFEM2D:

>> ./configure FC=gfortran --with-mpi
>> make



HOW TO RUN SPECFEM2D VALIDATION TEST

(requires 4 CPU cores, approximate run time 2 hours)


1. Following the instructions above, download and compile SPECFEM2D in a 
directory of your choice.


2. Navigate to the SPECFEM2D validation test directory:

>> cd mtuq_benchmarks/1D_tests/SPECFEM2D


3. Copy SPECFEM2D executables:

>> cp path/to/executables/{xmeshfem2D,xspecfem2D} bin/


4. Run the mesher executable:

>> mpirun -n 4 bin/xmeshfem2D


5. Run the solver executable:

>> mpirun -n 4 bin/xspecfem2D

